---
// src/pages/about.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About Us — Optical Illusion Lab" 
  description="Meet the team behind Optical Illusion Lab. Discover our mission to explore visual neuroscience, cognitive psychology, and the interactive science of visual tricks."
>
  <div class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-12">
    <div class="space-y-4 text-center">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-black tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white">
        About the Lab
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        We are a digital laboratory dedicated to investigating the boundary between objective physical stimuli and subjective human consciousness.
      </p>
      <div class="mx-auto h-1 w-20 rounded-full bg-purple-600"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-indigo dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          At the Optical Illusion Lab, our mission is to educate, entertain, and inspire curiosity about the human visual system. By providing interactive, real-time vector representations of classic and modern visual tricks, we allow users to directly manipulate parameters like speed, color contrast, and borders. This hands-on environment exposes the cognitive assumptions and neural pathways that govern daily sight.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">The Science of Sight</h2>
        <p>
          Sight is not a passive camera recording. The brain constantly interprets incomplete signals from the eyes, constructing a predictive model of the surrounding world to ensure quick decision-making. Optical illusions represent the edge cases where these speed-over-accuracy shortcuts fail. By analyzing why these patterns trip up our visual cortex, we gain vital insights into spatial coordination, light compensation, and neural latency.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Pure Vector Performance</h2>
        <p>
          Unlike legacy websites that rely on low-quality animated GIFs or video loops, our visual experiments are built with mathematically precise SVG elements and CSS styling. This ensures infinite scaling, zero pixelation, and lightweight performance, giving researchers and enthusiasts alike a true scientific tool to study human perception.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pt-6 text-center border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center space-x-2 rounded-xl bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-500 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-200">
        Return to Homepage
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
